        "text": "I’m thrilled to be co-leading the FORRT AI in Metascience Online Conference, and we would love your contributions :star-struck:\n\n:loudspeaker: *Call for Submissions — FORRT AI in Metascience Online Conference*\n\nHow can AI and large language models help us understand and improve how science works — and how are they changing science itself?\n\nJoin us *28–30 September 2026* (online and time-zone inclusive) for a global conversation at the intersection of *AI and meta-research*. The conference is free to attend, and talks will be shared on the FORRT YouTube channel.\n\nWe welcome contributions from all career stages and backgrounds: researchers, software engineers, librarians, and editors. Submit your contribution now (registration will open later in the summer).\n\n:bulb: Formats:\n• Research talks, symposia &amp; lightning talks\n• Workshops &amp; tutorials\n• Hackathons\n\n:spiral_calendar_pad: *Submission deadline: 31 July 2026*\n:page_facing_up: Details &amp; submission: <http:\/\/forrt.org\/ai-metascience|forrt.org\/ai-metascience>\n:speech_balloon: Questions? <mailto:l.wallrich@bbk.ac.uk|l.wallrich@bbk.ac.uk> or message Lukas Wallrich on the FORRT Slack\n\n#Metascience #OpenScience #AI #ReproducibleResearch\n\n :link:  <https:\/\/forrt.org\/ai-metascience\/>",
